(Corrects name of media company in first paragraph.)  Chinese provinces of Jiangsu, Jiangxi
and Zhejiang are having the worst drought in 60 years,  China 
News Service reported today, citing local governments.  Drought has reduced the water area in Fanyang lake, Chinaâ€™s
biggest fresh water lake in Jiangxi, by almost half, according
to the report. Rainfall in the first four months of the year in
Zhejiang was the smallest in 60 years, according to the report.
April rainfall in Jiangsu was the lowest in 60 years, the report
